codex
The Elasticsearch cluster is green with 3 nodes. I’m creating a namespace-local TLS secret for `es.example.com` and an `Ingress` using `ingressClassName: nginx`; the backend remains the existing `es-http` Service on port 9200.
  ✓ Inspect Elasticsearch pods, Service selector, and ingress controller address
  ✓ Fix es-http selector if it does not match running pod labels
  → Create TLS material and nginx Ingress for es.example.com
  • Verify cluster health plus HTTPS success and HTTP failure
exec
/bin/zsh -lc "set -e
openssl req -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey rsa:2048 \\
  -keyout /tmp/es.example.com.key \\
  -out /tmp/es.example.com.crt \\
  -subj \"/CN=es.example.com\" \\
  -addext \"subjectAltName=DNS:es.example.com\" >/dev/null 2>&1
kubectl create secret tls es-example-com-tls -n elasticsearch \\
  --cert=/tmp/es.example.com.crt \\
  --key=/tmp/es.example.com.key \\
  --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -
kubectl apply -f - <<'EOF'
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: es-http
  namespace: elasticsearch
  annotations:
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: \"true\"
    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/force-ssl-redirect: \"true\"
spec:
  ingressClassName: nginx
  tls:
  - hosts:
    - es.example.com
    secretName: es-example-com-tls
  rules:
  - host: es.example.com
    http:
      paths:
      - path: /
        pathType: Prefix
        backend:
          service:
            name: es-http
            port:
              number: 9200
EOF" in /Users/jinyige/Karma/runs/new-added-workflows/elasticsearch-http-selector-adversary-20260626_034809/stages/stage_01
